# Multi-Site AYA Oncology Reporting

## Overview

This project created a standardized adolescent and young adult oncology
reporting model across two hospital systems.

Although both hospitals required the same final Power BI measures, the
underlying EHR workflows differed significantly. Separate PostgreSQL extraction
pipelines were developed for each site, followed by harmonization into a common
patient-level reporting model.

## Hospital Workflow Differences

### Hospital A

- Cohort primarily identified through cancer registry and cancer-problem records
- Separate workflow required for deceased patients
- Referrals commonly identified through procedure orders
- Additional concepts derived from notes and SmartData Elements

### Hospital B

- Cohort primarily identified through oncology departments and encounters
- Registry diagnosis information supplemented encounter diagnoses
- Oral and IV chemotherapy required separate extraction workflows
- Radiation dates required parsing of multiple text formats
- Referrals were captured across referral, order, provider, note, and SmartData workflows

## Final Use

The standardized outputs supported a combined Power BI report while preserving
site-specific extraction logic.
